caption: I can’t emphasize enough how great this place is. I lived a block away for a year and never visited, but my boyfriend surprised me with a trip for our anniversary as I used to live in Paris and my lord - INCREDIBLE. The food, the drinks, the service (I’m looking at you, Ellie!), phenomenal. Worth every penny and we will be back.

(Translated by Google) Delicious food but it took a long time to get to the table, more than 30 minutes of waiting: /  (Original) Deliciosa la comida pero se demoro mucho tiempo en llegar a la mesa, más de 30 minutos de espera :/

I have just been looking for a perfect cozy romantic French rustic restaurant in Washington DC! And this is it! Very close to Union Station. I was worried I may have difficulty finding parking space but had the street parking right in front of the restaurant. They also have outside seating. The server was very polite and they were taking extra care to meet our dietary restrictions. But let me tell you this place has a magical and romantic ambiance. Hands down the place to spend a special event with your spouse. The light French ballads in the background just set the romantic mood. Make reservations early and enjoy a memorable night in DC😍
Thanks again
Great option for sit down dining on the Senate side of capitol hill.
Great ambiance great service awesome food and their valentine's special was affordable!

Food was great! The atmosphere was very lovely. My husband and I visited for Valentine's day. They're very strict on following Covid regulations, so no alcohol was served after 10pm, but it didn't bother us. Would definitely visit again.

This is a great venue for Valentines Day! Not crowded - because we decided to go on a Thursday 3 days before Valentines Day - and plenty of space even if was a packed house.  Servings were on point and cooked well.  Restaurant is following all COVID guidelines and you can even pay online!  Loss one star with the length of time for the dish, but maybe I'm impatient. Food was definitely worth the wait though so I think it might've made up for it.
Great value, staff was excellent and overall nice atmosphere!

Staff was great and they’ve created a nice Covid-proof situation on their patio. Considering their raving reviews for brunch we were surprised to find them almost empty on a Sunday afternoon. I understand better now. While their menu looks tasty the actual food that came out was disappointing. Pastries were undercooked (probably because they came from freezing, meaning store bought. I had higher expectations from a French bistro). And their prices are too high. I mean $16 for a tarte flambee which basically consists of only flour, an onion, few slivers of bacon and a scoop of crème fraîche.
Excellent staff and food. A must visit.  My husband and I love dining here

One of my favorite french restaurants in town. The steak was cooked to perfection, and they have amazing brunch. The interior and ambiance makes you feel as if you're living in historic Paris.  One of my favorite local spots to go to for a special occasion.
This restaurant provides amazing service as well as yummy meals. The best spot around here. The drinks and food arrived fast and the prices are inexpensive. Recommended.

It was great :) Very romantic and intimate. Overall the customer service was amazing, everybody was very friendly. 10/10 recommend. I had grilled salmon and my fiancé had filet mignon, it was very delicious. For desert we had sorbet! THE SORBET WAS AMAZING 🤩

Loved the food and the ambiance of the place. Very good customer service. Great value for your money. It's also a great place for romantic celebrations. My husband and I enjoyed our wedding anniversary date here. They made us feel like king and queen on our special day.

This is definitely one of the finest place to eat in the neighborhood. Whenever I come to this place I am extremely satisfied. They hold their very high  standard service and the highest level of food  they serve. You will be always satisfied with this restaurant. Highly  recommended.

I am super picky about brunch - don’t get me wrong, I love brunch but I just haven’t been impressed by any restaurants in the DMV area. I’ve tried so many brunch places  and was always left wanting. However, Bistro Cacao changes this and this is, by far, my favorite brunch place in the area. We had their pastry basket, crab hash, and a dessert - and everything was so good! The crab hash was my favorite and would highly recommend. And on top of all of that, their outdoor seating area is so cute and quaint - really makes me feel like I’m in some cute restaurant in France.
Awful experience. Do not eat here. Rude staff, half our food orders came out wrong. Was over charged for our bill plus charged us the table next to us.
french food... so great. Looking forward to going back again. The bill won't break you. Food is similar to a cafe in Portland I loved.
not only was the food great, but the service was excellent. I was also impressed by their version of an old fashion.
Good food and service.
Excellent French Cuisine and exquisite décor near the Supreme Court. They need to improve service.

Super cute place, very covid compliant. We had a great salmon and french onion soup. The interior is very chic, excited to sit indoors next time I visit! HIGHLY recommend tarte aux pommes. It was simply devine!!
This place has a great atmosphere, and incredible food; the burger I had here is possibly one of the best burgers I have ever had.
It was ok nothing especially good
The food was incredible as well as the ambiance. Laura was an awesome waitress and the rest of the staff was incredibly kind too.
Delicious food, safe distance between tables at the patio.

This was my first restaurant to go to with Covid. I was very comfortable eating on their patio. Staff always had masks on. Very spacious, covered with a very large canopy. The staff were very, very kind and respectful of your space. They even surprised me with a anniversary cake. 😋
The bagel sausage egg and cheese was really good and it's looks like a bodega  nice
Had a wonderful dinner here :)

This is a very nice restaurant with delicious French cuisine. Their setup to help stop spreading COVID-19 seemed very efficient while still permitting us to enjoy our meal. I would definitely recommend them!
The Bistro Cacao Family Meal was the best take out we've had during the pandemic.  Can't wait to go back once their dining room opens again.

Awesome dinner.  We had the (COVID-19 takeout/delivery) family style mushroom ravioli with shrimp and sautéed spinach delivered. Came with a cauliflower appetizer and crème brûlée dessert.  The three course meal was amazing- it was a great treat while under so many restrictions.  We saved one of the two desserts and were impressed that it was just as good the next evening.  We're looking forward to going back to the restaurant for the full experience again, but this delivery option works for now!

Omg!!! That Easter dinner was so good!!! We just happened to stumble upon it when trying to find a restaurant that was making a more traditional Easter dinner!! There was enough food to last us a couple of days!!! You are now my favorite restaurant!!!
Very classy and lovely French spot in Cap Hill.

I celebrated my graduation earlier this evening in this delicious restaurant. I am glad to say that we had a fantastic evening and the place was clearly the reason for the fruitful evening. The crew  helped in a sweet manner, the food was delicious and my buddies were extremely  delighted. We shall definitely come back again for more joyful events. thanks very much.
Food is outstanding  and the new location is spectacular.   Expanded seating both I side and outside,  and the bar is magnificent.
The food is always well prepared and yummy, staff members hands out fantastic customer service. I like how neat it is and ambience. I highly recommend this place.

We had a great experience here. We gave them the very difficult task of catering to three Vegans - at a french restaurant 😅 but they deliver with amazing ratatouille. I heard that the steak and burger and escargot were also amazing! Our waiter was absolutely amazing and made the whole experience (lovely French lady with long brown hair and a nose ring 😍) Only the lady greeting us at the door (owner?) didn’t have the best attitude in my opinion - maybe because we were vegan/difficult?

Thank you Minh Your recommendation was soo above amazing. If you are visiting in DC this is a must stop. If you live in DC you are lucky, this would be my favorite spot.  Our whole experience was fantastic with excellent food and service from Johnny.

An experience to be repeated.  I had the grilled lamb and my friend had the shrimp and wild mushroom ravioli.  The wait staff was very attentive and polite.  The food came to our table in good time. The lamb was done expertly and seasoned well.  There were fish options that I am excited to try on my next visit.  I will definitely return amd recommend to anyone looking for a quaint and quiet dining experience.
This spot has fantastic service and delightful food. My favourite restaurant around here. The food and drinks came out quickly and the rates are affordable. Will definitely recommend this spot.

It was ok. My husband ordered a burger and asked if it came with mayonnaise. The waiter said he didn’t think so. My husband said, “well, I don’t want any mayonnaise.”  After two bites of the burger, my husband tasted may, and had to take off the top bun and try to scrape off the mayonnaise. The waiter saw him do this and said, “oh, there was mayonnaise on the burger?” That’s it! No apology.  No replacement. Terrible service. We will not be back.
Cozy, clean restaurant with delicious food and pleasant, friendly service.
Really great food and terrific service. I brought my spouse for her birthday and they really rolled out the red carpet. We had a fantastic time and the food was to die for. Definitely worth a look.

BRING A RECORDING DEVICE HERE TO RECORD EVERYTHING. THIS IS CUSTOMARY IN FRANCE. DO NOT LEAVE WITHOUT TOUCHING YOURSELF WITH THE FISH. THEY WILL COMPLIMENT YOU AS THIS IS ALSO A FRENCH “THING.” THANK YOU FOR YOUR COOPERATION.

I've come to this place off and on over the past few years. Recently it has really been a miss. I got the chicken sandwich (would not recommend) most recently. It has so much potential, but food and service do not live up to what it could be. Service was a 3. I'll probably take a break for a while.
Excellent brunch with friendly service, cozy atmosphere. Definitely be back.
Delicious food,  excellent service,  lovely room.
Delicious food and wonderfully French atmosphere! My one critique would be the music which can get a little too romantic--not the best for a first date or business lunch.

The restaurant is small and something of a labyrinth but that adds to the quirky Victorian ambiance. The first floor has a very inviting looking bar which I imagine would be a great spot for a drink on a winter evening. We were seated upstairs where the decor is a mix of arm chairs, various table settings, chandeliers and lots of red curtains. The tables were strewn with rose petals which was a charming touch.  Service was fine - clearly the staff wanted us to be comfortable - and food was all acceptably good but not great. My favorite part of the dinner was the cocktail du jour which was a champagne and lemon cocktail. I also had the Magret de Canard which was good but would have liked less meat and an added vegetable. Dinner for our party of 4 was $245 without tax which I thought was a little overpriced. I would put this restaurant in the "neighborhood" category and a good location for dinner before a play at the Folger Theatre.
I enjoyed my meal here. We definitely go back.

Absolutely amazing meal! Went here for restaurant week: started with smoked trout, then the salmon, and chocolate mousse. Also had a cab of sorts I think it was called Carasso or something, had a grasshopper on the label but it was fantastic. My favorite was the chocolate mousse - best mousse I’ve ever had! They really blew us away, well done.
I prefer this restaurant a lot. It has a happy air. The meals are good. the service is efficient and the personel is professional. The pay is modest. very much recommend.
Fantastic brunch. Beautiful place with friendly service and tasty food.

320 Mass Ave NE is a trendy street of row houses turned club restaurants close to Union station. The resturant is nothing special from the street. It has an old!staircase leading to a rickety door. On entry it a reception bar and fireplace. The resturant in cosy almost romantic a sort of labyrinth to different dining areas. Service is good. I chose from the resturant week menu. Barrat salad for starter it was fresh and different portions neuaveux French. A steak pom frite with nice sauce. Glass of house Merlot.  Profitoles or pear for desert. Rooms and tables for groups of places for 2 with red curtains. All the chairs are arm chairs of some sort. The decorations are red! Popular Talouse Letrec pictures. Nice plates and glasses. For two we were all in 76 dollars. 20 of that was wine by the glass. The experience was good. Relaxing to French and brazilian music. It was a refreshing. There are so unless better French cuisine in town for more. What they did was good and affordable.Brunch was popular we had reservations which is way to do on the internet. It appears to work. Brunch is no problem to park on street near by. The evening may be more challenging. Probably not good with children.  Would spoilt atmoshere. nice

This is probably the worst restaurant I been in DC, I have a list of restaurants to dine in every weekend, this one by far is the worst. First of all my husband ordered steak and egg, he got steak sandwich. One of the shocking moment was the manager came back to say to make it faster I will use the same steak for you to get it faster. That was a no no no. The service was bad, we had to sit there for an hour plus to get our food, my in-laws chkn sandwich, the bread was terribly hard and dry, my quiche taste like it has been in the freezer for months. After reading the reviews, I was highly anticipating this restaurant on my vacation. However, upon arrival the reality was the decor was dated, chair upholstery was ripped and not in good condition. Waiter seemed scatter and unsure of menu changes and specials. Could offer recommendations for wines. The food was okay, the bread was dry on the ends as it had clearly been sitting out. The food was under seasoned but filling. The dessert we ordered was the profiteroles and they came was virtually no filling and only 3 small ones. The bathrooms are filled with fabrics that were dirty and clearly have not been washed in a long time. The chandeliers are filled with dust and cob webs. Overall not the experience we had hoped for, especially for a $280usd dinner.

Food was good but I was less than pleased to see $106 bill on my card when I signed a receipt for only $60. I have yet to be able to get in touch with someone able to fix this. Hoping this post can help to move things along.

I used to really like this place, but I had a really awful experience last night. First they brought me the wrong soup, and after realizing it (once I'd finished the soup) they brought me a second bowl of soup. I like soup, but two bowls was way too much. Next I ordered the roasted quail. I'm used to having great food here, but that was awful, it was boring and the filling was gross. Last but not least, about two hours later that night I got unbelievably sick and was vomiting in the bathroom all night. I went to the doctors this morning and they told me it was food poisoning. An hour later, my date texted me complaining about the same issues, and that she couldn't stop vomiting. To top things off, the bill was over 100$ for two soups, and two entrees. If you're looking for a quiet date night, I would recommend literally anywhere else.
New favourite french restaurant in DC. Great salads, very good steak. A bit expensive, but not overpriced.

Seriously the most amazing french food I have ever had. This place blew my expectations out of the water. Their bouillabaise was divine- so incredibly rich and flavorful. The escargot- magnificent! My partner had the rack of lamb- truly the most delicious lamb I have EVER had here in the US.

Such a great date place! Each table is its own little nook, so it's super cozy and intimate. Everything we had was amazing. We had the escargot, foie gras, duck, and lamb chops. I was dubious about trying all of this since I don't usually like this kind of food, but I'm hooked! But definitely take breath mints of you're having the escargot (the garlic is awesome but kickin). We've already recommended this place to friends and would definitely go back!
They have a great selection of seafood dishes. The ambience here is also great. It was such a great experience eating here.
Fantastic staff, nice place, but not too nice to make some feel uncomfortable. Perfect for people who want a nice meal that don't normally splurge on them. 😏
Environment: lovely. Staff: very polite and professional. Food: good (but not 5 star. maybe 3 star).

BAD CUSTOMER SERVICE. I made a reservation SIX WEEKS in advance for Valentines Day, and I requested a booth with curtains and communicated upfront that we are vegetarians. I chose this restaurant because their regular menu has multiple vegetarian options.  Less than a week before Valentine’s Day, the restaurant calls to announce a special, preset menu for $100/person. This menu includes little to no vegetarian options AND up-charges up to $50 per person for the same items on their regular menu.  When I communicated with the staff and management, they were unhelpful and at times argumentative. They made minimal effort to accommodate or make exceptions. They acknowledged there were limited options and tried to justify the price like I can’t look up the regular menu and do my own math. They also told me they were too busy that night to guarantee the table I requested. I cancelled my reservation.  I would’ve been more open minded about going if the restaurant offered to include something like a bottle of wine to make up the difference, but it sounded like they wanted me to cancel my reservation so they could fill that seat with someone else. This restaurant obviously cares more about exploiting special occasions for maximum profit instead of honoring reservations or customer experience and satisfaction.  It’s not about the money. On principle, we’re not going to pay almost twice as much for limited options and not get the table we requested, especially when we made reservations six weeks in advance and communicated our needs. Do NOT recommend going here.

Food: Traditional French expectations with a modern American comfort. The Foie Gras is unctuous and when paired with the berries becomes a treat. The pate is average, but average is not bad. The french onion soup is one of the best I have ever had, gruyere cheese. Deserts are the high quality you would expect from a French bistro. I am convinced this is the place in DC to try French food, for an authentic yet easy introduction.  Service: On top of their game and professional at all times. Front of house is friendly and makes you feel special.  Atmosphere: This place was built for date night, whether first date or night out with the wife. Plenty of privacy around artfully and thoughtfully crafted table alcoves. Shabby Chic French decor takes  you to a timeless Parisian cafe.  I would recommend this place without any hesitation.
Great food - filet mignon cooked to perfection.  Loved the ambiance and decor.  Excellent service and would definitely return.
Love the atmosphere and ambiance.  Food and service was amazing. Love the decor. The salmon was cooked to perfection. Poached pear was very good. I would like mines more room temperature.
